(1418187, 'A Princess of Mars', 'I am a very old man; how old I do not know. Possibly I am a hundred, possibly more; but I cannot tell because I have never aged as other men, nor do I remember any childhood. So far as I can recollect I have always been a man, a man of about thirty. I appear today as I did forty years and more ago, and yet I feel that I cannot go on living forever; that some day I shall die the real death from which there is no resurrection.\r\n[Adventures of John Carter in Mars -- from the author of the Tarzan se', 'Edgar Rice Burroughs', '9506915', 69.99, 9),
